  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best free WordPress plugins in 2014?",
  "response": "In 2014, several free WordPress plugins stood out for their functionality, reliability, and user-friendliness. Here's a list of some of the best free WordPress plugins from that year:\n\n1. **Yoast SEO**\n   - **Purpose:** SEO optimization\n   - **Description:** Yoast SEO helps you optimize your content for search engines. It offers features like XML sitemaps, meta tags, and content analysis to improve your site's SEO.\n\n2. **Jetpack**\n   - **Purpose:** All-in-one functionality\n   - **Description:** Jetpack is a versatile plugin that provides a suite of tools including site stats, security, performance enhancements, and social sharing features.\n\n3. **W3 Total Cache**\n   - **Purpose:** Performance optimization\n   - **Description:** This plugin helps improve your site's speed and performance by caching pages, minifying CSS and JavaScript, and optimizing images.\n\n4. **Contact Form 7**\n   - **Purpose:** Contact forms\n   - **Description:** A popular plugin for creating and managing multiple contact forms. It's simple to use and highly customizable.\n\n5. **Akismet**\n   - **Purpose:** Spam protection\n   - **Description:** Akismet helps protect your site from spam comments and trackbacks, keeping your comment sections clean and manageable.\n\n6. **Wordfence Security**\n   - **Purpose:** Security\n   - **Description:** Wordfence offers a robust security solution, including firewall protection, malware scanning, and login security.\n\n7. **NextGEN Gallery**\n   - **Purpose:** Photo galleries\n   - **Description:** A powerful tool for creating and managing photo galleries on your WordPress site, with options for slideshows and albums.\n\n8. **Google XML Sitemaps**\n   - **Purpose:** Sitemap creation\n   - **Description:** This plugin automatically generates a sitemap for your site, helping search engines index your content more effectively.\n\n9. **TinyMCE Advanced**\n   - **Purpose:** Text editor enhancement\n   - **Description:** Enhances the WordPress text editor with additional formatting options and tools, making content creation more efficient.\n\n10. **WP Super Cache**\n    - **Purpose:** Caching\n    - **Description:** Another powerful caching plugin that helps improve your site's performance by generating static HTML files from your dynamic WordPress site.\n\nThese plugins were widely recommended and used in 2014 for their effectiveness in enhancing various aspects of WordPress sites, from SEO to security and performance.",
